docs.abstract: The unemployment rate for black workers hit its lowest point on record recently. But even a strong labor market has limits in spreading opportunity widely.
docs.snippet: The unemployment rate for black workers hit its lowest point on record recently. But even a strong labor market has limits in spreading opportunity widely.
docs.lead_paragraph: President Trump celebrated the milestone on Twitter and in his State of the Union address. The unemployment rate for black Americans had hit its lowest point on record, a sign that the recovery was at last reaching groups that had been left behind.

headline.main: Lowest Ever Black Jobless Rate Is Still Twice That of Whites
headline.print_headline: The Limitations of a Rising Tide

byline.original: By Natalie Kitroeff and Ben Casselman

docs.abstract: Many economists see deals offering tax breaks to attract corporate sites as inefficient, expensive and ultimately ineffective.
docs.snippet: Many economists see deals offering tax breaks to attract corporate sites as inefficient, expensive and ultimately ineffective.
docs.lead_paragraph: When New Jersey announced a $7 billion package of tax incentives to try to lure Amazon’s second headquarters to Newark, local officials saw a chance to jump-start a city that has long struggled with poverty and joblessness.

headline.main: Promising Billions to Amazon: Is It a Good Deal for Cities?
headline.print_headline: Risks for Cities In Sweetening  Amazon’s Pot

docs.abstract: The possible appointment of Andrew Smith, who represented Facebook, Uber and Equifax and others, raised the prospect of frequent recusals from investigations.
docs.snippet: The possible appointment of Andrew Smith, who represented Facebook, Uber and Equifax and others, raised the prospect of frequent recusals from investigations.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Federal Trade Commission is expected to appoint an industry lawyer who has represented Facebook, Uber and Equifax to lead the agency’s consumer protection bureau tasked with policing those companies.

headline.main: Industry Lawyer Expected to Head F.T.C. Consumer Protection
headline.print_headline: Industry Lawyer Is Said to Be Expected to Lead F.T.C. Consumer Protection

docs.abstract: Apple hopes a new $299 iPad for schools and other new software tools will help it catch Google in the hunt for students’ attention.
docs.snippet: Apple hopes a new $299 iPad for schools and other new software tools will help it catch Google in the hunt for students’ attention.
docs.lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — Apple unveiled a new iPad aimed at classrooms and other education tools on Tuesday, in a bid to catch up to Google for students’ attention — and win more school districts’ dollars.

headline.main: Apple Unveils New iPad to Catch Google in the Classroom
headline.print_headline: Apple Takes Aim at Google At the Head of the Class

byline.original: By Jack Nicas and Natasha Singer

docs.abstract: Even though Mr. Trump still takes potshots at Amazon, the industry’s relationship with the White House is shifting as tech companies find some common ground with the president.
docs.snippet: Even though Mr. Trump still takes potshots at Amazon, the industry’s relationship with the White House is shifting as tech companies find some common ground with the president.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Two days after Donald J. Trump won the 2016 election, executives at Google consoled their employees in an all-staff meeting broadcast around the world.

headline.main: Silicon Valley Warms to Trump After a Chilly Start
headline.print_headline: Silicon Valley,  Wary of Trump,  Warms to Him

docs.abstract: After selling their robotics company to Google, two engineers are working on technology they think can change how special effects are made.
docs.snippet: After selling their robotics company to Google, two engineers are working on technology they think can change how special effects are made.
docs.lead_paragraph: PALO ALTO, Calif. — Inside an old auto body shop here in Silicon Valley, Stefan Avalos pushed a movie camera down a dolly track.

headline.main: Lights, Camera, Artificial Action: Start-Up Is Taking A.I. to the Movies
headline.print_headline: A.I. Takes a Lead Role In Making Visual Effects

docs.abstract: After changing the fundamental idea of chip design, former academics Dave Patterson and John Hennessy have received “the Nobel Prize of computing.”
docs.snippet: After changing the fundamental idea of chip design, former academics Dave Patterson and John Hennessy have received “the Nobel Prize of computing.”
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — In 1980, Dave Patterson, a computer science professor, looked at the future of the world’s digital machines and saw their limits.

headline.main: Computer Chip Visionaries Win Turing Award
headline.print_headline: Chip Design Visionaries Share Turing Award

docs.abstract: The internet giant developed the tensor processing units, or T.P.U.s, for its data centers. Now other companies can use them through its cloud-computing service.
docs.snippet: The internet giant developed the tensor processing units, or T.P.U.s, for its data centers. Now other companies can use them through its cloud-computing service.
docs.lead_paragraph: MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif. — A few years ago, Google created a new kind of computer chip to help power its giant artificial intelligence systems. These chips were designed to handle the complex processes that some believe will be a key to the future of the computer industry.

headline.main: Google Makes Its Special A.I. Chips Available to Others
headline.print_headline: Google Is Making Its Special A.I. Chips Available to Others via Cloud Computing

docs.abstract: The Microsoft co-founder will give $125 million to his nonprofit research lab to help develop technology that adds common sense to artificial intelligence.
docs.snippet: The Microsoft co-founder will give $125 million to his nonprofit research lab to help develop technology that adds common sense to artificial intelligence.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Microsoft’s co-founder Paul Allen said Wednesday that he was pumping an additional $125 million into his nonprofit computer research lab for an ambitious new effort to teach machines “common sense.”

headline.main: Paul Allen Wants to Teach Machines Common Sense
headline.print_headline: A.I.’s Greatest Challenge: Digitizing Common Sense

docs.abstract: With a new cloud-computing service, businesses can build their own artificial intelligence algorithms, even if they have little experience with the technology.
docs.snippet: With a new cloud-computing service, businesses can build their own artificial intelligence algorithms, even if they have little experience with the technology.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Google has been using artificial intelligence to build other artificially intelligent systems for the last several months.

headline.main: Google Sells A.I. for Building A.I. (Novices Welcome)
headline.print_headline: Google Selling A.I. Technology That Helps Others Create A.I.
